<p class="date">April 21, 2006</p>
<p>Michael was tired, and didn't want to hunt down Pharmacity with me.  But I needed something to wash my face, and so walked down Avenida de Mayo in search of an outlet of the pharmacy megastore which seemed so ubiquitous until I went looking for one.</p>
<p>My head was still full of the Pugliese I'd danced to in class just a few minutes before, and I strolled with refined rhythm.   At a wide corner a man about my age or slightly older, dressed in a business suit, glanced at me, angled his torso just a little towards me, and said:</p>
<p><em>&iexcl;Marronita!</em></p>
<p>He then straightened his shoulders and continued on his way.</p>
<p>
And I, wearing my brown overcoat, with my brown hair, got the joke, understood the teasing, affectionate remark:  I, the cute little brown-haired one.   I smiled and continued on my own way, savoring the <em>piropo</em>.</p>